<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="95" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[189,797,1576,1921]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,327,1648,1672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name, used as a noun in apposition, honors the early Ainu culture once known from the area of the 
<typeStatus box="[516,568,1720,1744]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[189,797,1576,1921]" lastBlockId="1.[835,1443,1540,1920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,319,1754,1778]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is one of at least four Japanese species without the distinctive pair of small knobs found on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kawai" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[381,472,1827,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Perlomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parva">
<emphasis box="[381,472,1827,1850]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">P. parva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and several other members of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Kawai, T." box="[352,493,1861,1885]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" refId="ref3856" refString="Kawai, T. 1967. Fauna Japonica. Plecoptera (Insecta). Biogeographical Society of Japan, Tokyo. 211 pp." type="book" year="1967">Kawai 1967</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nelson, C. H. &amp; J. F. Hanson" box="[506,784,1861,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" pagination="187 - 199" refId="ref3983" refString="Nelson, C. H. &amp; J. F. Hanson. 1973. The genus Perlomyia (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 46: 187 - 199." type="journal article" year="1973">Nelson &amp; Hanson 1973</bibRefCitation>
); we are uncertain about the presence of these structures on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kohno" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[999,1126,1541,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Perlomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gifuensis">
<emphasis box="[999,1126,1541,1565]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">P. gifuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This new species is easily distinguished from other Japanese species by the presence of a truncate lobe on male tergum 8 and by the small apical spine on the male cerci. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivec &amp; Stark" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Perlomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kersti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Perlomyia kersti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described below, is the only other Japanese species known to have a male tergal lobe and in that species the dorsal lobe is located on tergum 9. At least two other Asian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1906" box="[1140,1249,1789,1813]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Perlomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1140,1249,1789,1813]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">Perlomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zhiltzova 1975)" baseAuthorityName="Zhiltzova" baseAuthorityYear="1975" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Perlomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levanidovae">
<emphasis box="[1276,1443,1789,1813]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">P. levanidovae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zhiltzova, L. A." box="[843,1023,1824,1849]" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" pagination="221 - 230" refId="ref4197" refString="Zhiltzova, L. A. 1975. Rhopalopsole, a new for the USSR genus of stoneflies (Plecoptera, Leuctridae). Zoologischesky Zhurnal, 54: 221 - 230. [Russian]" type="journal article" year="1975">Zhiltzova 1975</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nelson &amp; Hanson 1973" authorityName="Nelson &amp; Hanson" authorityYear="1973" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Perlomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithae">
<emphasis box="[1097,1214,1825,1849]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="95">P. smithae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nelson, C. H. &amp; J. F. Hanson" pageId="1" pageNumber="95" pagination="187 - 199" refId="ref3983" refString="Nelson, C. H. &amp; J. F. Hanson. 1973. The genus Perlomyia (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 46: 187 - 199." type="journal article" year="1973">Nelson &amp; Hanson 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, lack knobs on male tergum 10, but these species also lack dorsal lobes on segment 8.
</paragraph>
